In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups
water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and finely dice half the @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and diced); 
thinly slice remaining bell pepper into strips. Drain @mango{4%oz},
reserving juice. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled,
and finely diced). Mince some of the diced onion until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP
for 4 servings); set aside for step 5. Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Zest and quarter
@lime{1}(zested and quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1/2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add diced bell pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add mango and
cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add 1/4 cup water and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings); cook until liquid
has mostly evaporated, ~{30%seconds}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1 1/2%tsp} in same pan over
medium-high heat. Add diced onion and sliced bell pepper; season with @salt{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt (we used 1/2 tsp;
1 tsp for 4 servings), and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in reserved mango juice and
cook until thickened, ~{30%seconds}. Remove from heat. Taste and season with
salt and pepper.

> Cook through this step as instructed, swapping in beef or organic beef
for pork.

To bowl with mango mixture, add tomato, minced onion, juice from one
lime (juice from 1 1/2 limes for 4 servings; add a bit more if desired), and a
large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}; stir to combine. Taste and season
generously with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with pork, salsa, and @guacamole{4%tbsp} in
separate sections. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.